下午好  我是夏洛克·克福尔摩斯
Good afternoon. I am Sherlock Holmes,

182
00:08:59,880 --> 00:09:01,940
这是我的朋友兼同事  华生医生
this is my friend and colleague, Dr Watson.

183
00:09:01,950 --> 00:09:02,990
你可以在他面前畅所欲言
You may speak freely in front of him,

184
00:09:02,990 --> 00:09:04,930
- 因为他基本听不懂  - 福尔摩斯
- as he rarely understands a word. - Holmes!

185
00:09:04,930 --> 00:09:05,730
但在你开口之前
However, before you do,

186
00:09:05,730 --> 00:09:08,030
容我先说说我的几点观察
allow me to make some trifling observations.

187
00:09:08,300 --> 00:09:09,680
你有一种恶作剧般的幽默感
You have an impish sense of humour,

188
00:09:09,680 --> 00:09:11,100
你现在就在以此
which currently you are deploying

189
00:09:11,100 --> 00:09:13,670
减轻你个人的痛苦
to ease a degree of personal anguish.

190
00:09:13,690 --> 00:09:14,890
你最近嫁给了一个
You have recently married a man

191
00:09:14,890 --> 00:09:17,040
看起来性情温和的人
of a seemingly kindly disposition,

192
00:09:17,120 --> 00:09:19,150
而他现在为一个
who has now abandoned you

193
00:09:19,150 --> 00:09:21,900
品行有问题的同伴而抛弃了你
for an unsavoury companion of dubious morals.

194
00:09:21,950 --> 00:09:24,300
你把来到这里当做最后的手段
You have come to this agency as a last resort,

195
00:09:24,300 --> 00:09:26,790
以期你们的关系可以得到调解
in the hope that reconciliation may still be possible.

196
00:09:26,790 --> 00:09:28,350
我的天啊  福尔摩斯
Good Lord, Holmes!

197
00:09:28,490 --> 00:09:32,260
当然  所有这些都是从你的香水推测得来
All of this is, of course, perfectly evident from your perfume.

198
00:09:34,420 --> 00:09:35,510
她的香水
Her perfume?

199
00:09:35,810 --> 00:09:39,210
对  香水  让我洞悉一切  却给你带来灾难
Yes, her perfume, which brings insight to me and disaster to you.

200
00:09:39,210 --> 00:09:40,230
为什么
How so?

201
00:09:40,520 --> 00:09:42,510
因为我认出了它
Because I recognised it

202
00:09:43,150 --> 00:09:44,370
而你没有
and you did not.

203
00:09:45,120 --> 00:09:46,750
- 玛丽  - 约翰
- Mary! - John.

204
00:09:47,310 --> 00:09:50,360
苍天在上  你为什么要扮成客户
Why, in God's name, are you pretending to be a client?

205
00:09:50,360 --> 00:09:54,940
因为我想不出别的办法能见我丈夫  丈夫
Because I could think of no other way to see my husband, husband.

206
00:09:57,540 --> 00:09:59,920
那是个国际阴谋事件
It was an affair of international intrigue.

207
00:09:59,920 --> 00:10:01,920
就是个被谋杀的乡绅
It was a murdered country squire.

208
00:10:01,920 --> 00:10:03,250
不管怎样  事情紧急
Nevertheless, matters were pressing.

209
00:10:03,250 --> 00:10:05,090
我不介意你走  亲爱的
I don't mind you going, my darling,

210
00:10:05,090 --> 00:10:07,600
- 我介意的是你扔下我  - 但你能做什么
- I mind you leaving me behind. - But what could you do?!

211
00:10:07,600 --> 00:10:08,690
那你能做什么
Well, what do you do,

212
00:10:08,690 --> 00:10:11,780
除了晃来晃去做笔记  时不时目瞪口呆
except wander around taking notes, looking surprised?!

213
00:10:11,780 --> 00:10:12,760
够了
Enough!

214
00:10:14,750 --> 00:10:17,680
舞台已经准备好  大幕升起
The stage is set, the curtain rises.

215
00:10:18,810 --> 00:10:20,240
我们可以开始了
We are ready to begin.

216
00:10:21,260 --> 00:10:22,610
开始什么
Begin what?

217
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:26,540
有时为了破一个案子  必须先破另一个
Sometimes to solve a case, one must first solve another.

218
00:10:26,540 --> 00:10:28,210
你有案子吗  新案子
Oh, you have a case, then, a new one?

219
00:10:28,210 --> 00:10:30,190
一个老案子  非常老
An old one, very old.

220
00:10:32,360 --> 00:10:33,870
我必须得深入
I shall have to go deep.

221
00:10:34,250 --> 00:10:35,460
深入什么
Deep? Into what?

222
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:37,320
我自己
Myself.

223
00:10:39,880 --> 00:10:42,430
雷斯垂德  别在门外晃了  进来吧
Lestrade! Do stop loitering by the door and come in.

224
00:10:44,650 --> 00:10:45,910
你怎么知道是我
How did you know it was me?

225
00:10:45,910 --> 00:10:48,010
脚步声是不会错的
The regulation tread is unmistakable.

226
00:10:48,010 --> 00:10:50,470
比琼斯轻  被格雷格森重
Lighter than Jones, heavier than Gregson.

227
00:10:50,720 --> 00:10:54,200
我刚上来  哈德森太太不肯说话
I, I just came up... Mrs Hudson didn't seem to be talking.

228
00:10:54,570 --> 00:10:58,310
恐怕她是在用讽刺的方法进行文学批评
I fear she has branched into literary criticism by means of satire.

229
00:10:58,310 --> 00:11:00,850
这是当代房东恼人的发展趋势
It is a distressing trend in the modern landlady.

230
00:11:01,240 --> 00:11:03,710
你为何事在下班时间过来
What brings you here in your off-duty hours?

231
00:11:04,420 --> 00:11:07,000
- 你怎么知道我下班了  - 你到了之后
- How do you know I'm off duty? - Well, since your arrival,

232
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:09,420
超过40%的注意力都在我的酒瓶上
you've addressed over 40% of your remarks to my decanter.

233
00:11:09,420 --> 00:11:11,950
华生  给探长拿点他显然想要的东西
Watson, give the Inspector what he so clearly wants.

234
00:11:13,840 --> 00:11:18,480
雷斯垂德  我们能为你做什么
So...Lestrade, what can we do for you?

235
00:11:18,710 --> 00:11:21,890
我不是为公事来的  我只是想过来看看
Oh, I'm not here on business, I just thought I'd drop by.

236
00:11:22,750 --> 00:11:23,970
社交拜访吗
A social call?

237
00:11:24,140 --> 00:11:27,680
当然  只是想给你带来节日问候
Yeah, of course, just to wish you the compliments of the season.

238
00:11:31,240 --> 00:11:34,410
- 圣诞快乐  - 圣诞快乐
- Merry Christmas. - Merry Christmas.

239
00:11:34,410 --> 00:11:35,180
可算客套完了
Thank God that's over.

240
00:11:35,180 --> 00:11:38,240
说吧  探长  是什么奇怪的事让你来到我家
Now, Inspector, what strange happening compels you to my door,

241
00:11:38,240 --> 00:11:40,140
又尴尬得说不出口
but embarrasses you to relate?

242
00:11:40,800 --> 00:11:42,180
谁说出事了
Who said anything happened?

243
00:11:42,180 --> 00:11:45,590
你  虽然你没有真正说出来
You did. By every means short of actual speech.

244
00:11:46,940 --> 00:11:50,200
福尔摩斯  你误判了
Holmes, you have misdiagnosed.

245
00:11:50,640 --> 00:11:52,160
那纠正我一下  医生
Then, correct me, Doctor.

246
00:11:53,090 --> 00:11:56,560
他不是想要喝一杯  而是需要喝一杯
He didn't want a drink, he needed one.

247
00:11:57,460 --> 00:12:00,430
他不是尴尬  他是害怕
He's not embarrassed, he's afraid.

248
00:12:02,870 --> 00:12:06,600
我的传记作者有进步啊  成长得真快
My Boswell is learning. They do grow up so fast.

249
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,440
华生  给苏格兰场壮壮胆子
Watson, restore the courage of Scotland Yard.

250
00:12:09,470 --> 00:12:11,010
探长  坐下吧
Inspector, do sit down.

251
00:12:12,410 --> 00:12:15,420
我并不是害怕
I'm, I'm not afraid, exactly.

252
00:12:15,560 --> 00:12:17,640
恐惧是面对危险时的智慧
Fear is wisdom in the face of danger,

253
00:12:17,640 --> 00:12:19,440
这没什么难为情的
it is nothing to be ashamed of.

254
00:12:20,950 --> 00:12:21,820
谢谢
Thank you.

255
00:12:21,820 --> 00:12:23,140
从头开始讲吧
From the beginning, then.

256
00:12:29,450 --> 00:12:30,530
你
You!

257
00:12:31,320 --> 00:12:32,840
不要  拜托
No, please!

258
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:42,900
你
You?!

259
00:12:46,950 --> 00:12:48,030
等一下
A moment.

260
00:12:56,060 --> 00:12:57,290
这是什么时候的事
When was this?

261
00:12:58,600 --> 00:12:59,920
昨天早上
Yesterday morning.

262
00:13:00,780 --> 00:13:02,930
那个新娘的脸  是怎样描述的
The bride's face, how was it described?

263
00:13:06,110 --> 00:13:10,730
"像死人一样苍白  嘴像一道绯红的伤口"
"White as death, mouth like a crimson wound."

264
00:13:14,690 --> 00:13:16,250
这是编造还是事实
Poetry or truth?

265
00:13:17,320 --> 00:13:18,950
很多人会说它们是一样的
Many would say they're the same thing.

266
00:13:18,950 --> 00:13:21,820
对  他们都是白痴  编造还是事实
Yes, idiots. Poetry or truth?

267
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:26,550
我看到过她的脸  是在后来
I saw her face myself. Afterwards.

268
00:13:27,090 --> 00:13:28,200
什么的后来
After what?

269
00:13:28,200 --> 00:13:29,310
你
You?

270
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,420
还是我
Or me?

271
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:43,210
不是吧  雷斯垂德  一个女人当众饮弹
Oh, really, Lestrade, a woman blows her own brains out in public

272
00:13:43,220 --> 00:13:45,750
你还需要我帮忙找出罪犯
and you need help identifying the guilty party?

273
00:13:46,110 --> 00:13:48,930
恐怕苏格兰场又刷低了下限
I feel Scotland Yard has reached a new low.

274
00:13:49,200 --> 00:13:50,690
那不是我来的原因
That's not why I'm here.

275
00:13:50,690 --> 00:13:53,440
- 我猜也是  - 她叫什么名字  那个新娘
- I surmised. - What was her name, the bride?

276
00:13:54,120 --> 00:13:57,060
艾米丽娅·瑞克莱蒂  昨天是她的结婚纪念日
Emelia Ricoletti. Yesterday was her wedding anniversary.

277
00:13:57,060 --> 00:13:59,500
当然  有人报了警
The police, of course, were called.

278
00:14:00,310 --> 00:14:02,880
她的尸体被送到了停尸房
And her body taken to the morgue.

279
00:14:03,030 --> 00:14:05,960
这是标准程序  你为什么要告诉我们猜得到的事
Standard procedure. Why are you telling us what may be presumed?

280
00:14:07,660 --> 00:14:09,520
因为接下来发生的事
Because of what happened next.

281
00:14:11,310 --> 00:14:14,960
几小时之后  在莱姆豪斯
Limehouse. Just a few hours later.

282
00:14:26,790 --> 00:14:30,730
托马斯·瑞克莱蒂  艾米丽娅·瑞克莱蒂的丈夫
Thomas Ricoletti. Emelia Ricoletti's husband.

283
00:14:31,240 --> 00:14:34,550
大概是在去停尸房辨认遗体的路上吧
Presumably on his way to the morgue to identify her remains?

284
00:14:36,590 --> 00:14:39,050
结果他省了这麻烦
As it turned out, he was saved the trip.

285
00:14:45,100 --> 00:14:49,750
*别忘了我*
*Do not forget me*

286
00:14:50,140 --> 00:14:54,220
*别忘了我*
*Do not forget me*

287
00:14:54,890 --> 00:14:58,010
*记住那少女*
*Remember the maid...*

288
00:14:57,490 --> 00:14:58,720
你是谁
Who are you?

289
00:14:59,050 --> 00:15:02,350
*磨坊的少女*
*The maid of the mill...*

290
00:14:59,440 --> 00:15:03,140
你为什么要这样做  告诉我你是谁
Why are you doing this? Just tell me who you are!

291
00:15:03,590 --> 00:15:06,510
你听出了我们的歌吗  亲爱的
You recognise our song, my dear?

292
00:15:07,360 --> 00:15:09,600
我在婚礼上唱过
I sang it at our wedding.

293
00:15:14,610 --> 00:15:15,790
艾米丽娅
Emelia?

294
00:15:16,810 --> 00:15:20,430
你死了  你不可能在这里  你死了
You, you're dead, you can't be here, you died!

295
00:15:21,050 --> 00:15:23,280
我美吧  托马斯
Am I not beautiful, Thomas?

296
00:15:23,630 --> 00:15:26,600
跟你娶我那天一样美
As beautiful as the day you married me?

297
00:15:26,980 --> 00:15:28,560
- 谁...  - 这是怎么回事
- Who... - What the hell is all this about?!

298
00:15:30,750 --> 00:15:34,210
你说看起来像什么  我英俊的朋友
What does it look like, my handsome friend?

299
00:15:36,460 --> 00:15:38,150
这是枪杆下的婚礼[原意:奉子成婚]
It's a shotgun wedding.

300
00:15:47,520 --> 00:15:50,970
直至死亡将我们分离  他们各死了一次
Till death us do part. Twice in this case.

301
00:16:08,860 --> 00:16:10,020
真离奇
Extraordinary.

302
00:16:10,940 --> 00:16:12,400
不可能
Impossible.

303
00:16:13,060 --> 00:16:13,790
太棒了
Superb.

304
00:16:13,790 --> 00:16:15,670
当街自杀  尸体杀人
Suicide as street theatre, murder by corpse.

305
00:16:15,670 --> 00:16:16,910
雷斯垂德  你简直宠坏我们了
Lestrade, you're spoiling us.

306
00:16:16,910 --> 00:16:18,110
华生  拿上帽子和外套
Watson, your hat and coat.

307
00:16:18,110 --> 00:16:19,310
- 我们去哪里  - 停尸房
- Where are we going? - To the morgue.

308
00:16:19,320 --> 00:16:20,800
一刻也不能耽搁了
There's not a moment to lose,

309
00:16:21,120 --> 00:16:23,490
很少有人会这样说停尸房
which one can so rarely say of a morgue.

310
00:16:23,630 --> 00:16:24,670
那我就坐在这里吗
And am I just to sit here?

311
00:16:24,680 --> 00:16:27,500
当然不了  亲爱的  我们之后会饿的
Not at all, my dear. We'll be hungry later.

312
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:30,220
福尔摩斯  有个问题  穿花呢衣服去停尸房吗
Holmes, just one thing, tweeds in a morgue?

313
00:16:30,220 --> 00:16:32,690
没时间换衣服了  华生
Needs must when the devil drives, Watson.

314
00:16:36,040 --> 00:16:37,090
再见  夫人
Ma'am.

315
00:16:37,670 --> 00:16:39,840
我参与了一项活动
I'm part of a campaign, you know.

316
00:16:39,840 --> 00:16:41,220
活动
Oh, campaign?

317
00:16:41,680 --> 00:16:42,960
为女性争取投票权
Votes for women.

318
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:46,210
你是支持还是反对
And are you for or against?

319
00:16:46,690 --> 00:16:47,840
出去
Get out.

320
00:17:03,940 --> 00:17:05,820
他们又走了  对吧
Have they gone off again, have they?

321
00:17:06,450 --> 00:17:09,950
那些先生们过着什么样的生活啊
I don't know, what a life those gentlemen lead.

322
00:17:09,950 --> 00:17:12,840
是啊  那些先生们
Yes. Those gentlemen!

323
00:17:13,360 --> 00:17:14,770
算了
Never you mind.

324
00:17:15,030 --> 00:17:17,670
差点忘了  这是给你的
Almost forgot, that came for you.

325
00:17:24,430 --> 00:17:26,870
速来

326
00:17:27,170 --> 00:17:30,930
赫德森太太  告诉我丈夫我会晚归
Mrs Hudson, tell my husband I'll be home late,

327
00:17:31,210 --> 00:17:33,140
我有些急事
I have some urgent business.

328
00:17:33,190 --> 00:17:34,530
一切还好吧
Is everything all right?

329
00:17:34,540 --> 00:17:37,660
只是有个朋友需要帮助
Oh, you know, just a, er, friend in need.

330
00:17:37,660 --> 00:17:39,790
天啊  什么朋友
Oh, dear. What friend?

331
00:17:40,550 --> 00:17:41,750
英格兰
England.

332
00:17:44,090 --> 00:17:47,860
还真是含糊
Well, that's not very specific.

333
00:17:51,250 --> 00:17:52,850
停尸房谁当班
Who's on mortuary duty?

334
00:17:54,190 --> 00:17:55,150
你知道的
You know who.

335
00:17:55,150 --> 00:17:56,550
总是他
Always him.

336
00:18:04,090 --> 00:18:06,280
拜托告诉我这是哪个白痴干的
Please tell me which idiot did this!

337
00:18:09,360 --> 00:18:11,470
这是为了大家的安全
It's for everyone's safety.

338
00:18:14,240 --> 00:18:16,960
这女人死了  她半边头都不见了
This woman is dead, half her head is missing.

339
00:18:16,960 --> 00:18:18,710
她对谁都不是威胁
She's not a threat to anyone.

340
00:18:18,870 --> 00:18:21,860
跟她的丈夫说去吧  他在那边的罩单下
Tell that to her husband, he's under a sheet over there.

341
00:18:21,860 --> 00:18:23,240
不管昨晚在莱姆豪斯发生了什么
Whatever happened in Limehouse last night,

342
00:18:23,240 --> 00:18:26,490
都可以断定那不是一个死去的女人干的
I think we can safely assume it wasn't the work of a dead woman.

343
00:18:26,910 --> 00:18:29,130
比这更奇怪的事都发生过
Stranger things have happened.

344
00:18:29,590 --> 00:18:30,760
比如呢
Such as...?

345
00:18:31,100 --> 00:18:34,240
就是...奇怪的事
Well... Strange things.

346
00:18:34,240 --> 00:18:35,840
你说话跟小孩一样
You're speaking like a child.

347
00:18:35,840 --> 00:18:38,030
这显然是活人干的  他去哪了
This is clearly man's work. Where is he?

348
00:18:42,770 --> 00:18:43,820
福尔摩斯
Holmes.

349
00:18:46,060 --> 00:18:47,110
霍普
Hooper.

350
00:18:50,500 --> 00:18:52,640
你  继续工作
You, back to work!

351
00:18:53,900 --> 00:18:58,540
你是来变戏法震撼我们了吧
So, come to astonish us with your magic tricks, I suppose?

352
00:18:58,540 --> 00:19:00,790
你想提醒我注意什么吗
Is there anything to which you would like to draw my attention?

353
00:19:00,790 --> 00:19:02,650
完全没有  福尔摩斯先生
Nothing at all, Mr Holmes.

354
00:19:03,420 --> 00:19:05,900
你想什么时候走都行
You may leave any time you like.

355
00:19:06,000 --> 00:19:09,460
霍普医生  是我请福尔摩斯先生来的  合作点
Dr Hooper, I asked Mr Holmes to come here. Cooperate.

356
00:19:09,460 --> 00:19:10,730
这是命令
That's an order.

357
00:19:13,380 --> 00:19:14,800
有两点"值得注意"
There are two "features of interest",

358
