885
00:46:00,100 --> 00:46:01,450
我非常想给你的编辑写信
Well, I've a good mind to write to your editor.

886
00:46:01,460 --> 00:46:03,030
你是一个活生生的人
You are a living, breathing man.

887
00:46:03,140 --> 00:46:05,800
- 你也有生活  也有过去  - 有什么
- You've lived a life, you have a past. - A what?!

888
00:46:05,800 --> 00:46:07,760
- 你肯定有过...  - 有什么
- Well, you must have had... - Had what?

889
00:46:10,070 --> 00:46:11,370
- 你懂的  - 不懂
- You know. - No.

890
00:46:13,220 --> 00:46:14,480
经历
Experiences.

891
00:46:14,640 --> 00:46:17,190
把左轮手枪递给我  我突然需要用一下
Pass me your revolver, I have a sudden need to use it.

892
00:46:17,200 --> 00:46:19,060
见鬼  福尔摩斯  你也是血肉之躯
Damn it, Holmes, you are flesh and blood,

893
00:46:19,070 --> 00:46:21,000
也有感情  你有...
you have feelings, you have...

894
00:46:21,000 --> 00:46:24,300
你肯定有...冲动
You must have... impulses.

895
00:46:24,300 --> 00:46:26,030
天啊  我从未如此盼望
Dear Lord, I have never been so impatient

896
00:46:26,030 --> 00:46:27,880
被杀人不眨眼的鬼魂攻击
to be attacked by a murderous ghost.

897
00:46:27,880 --> 00:46:32,180
作为你的朋友  作为担心你的人
As your friend, as someone who worries about you...

898
00:46:33,960 --> 00:46:35,430
是什么让你变成这样的
What made you like this?

899
00:46:37,620 --> 00:46:39,000
华生...
Oh, Watson...

900
00:46:40,970 --> 00:46:42,840
没什么塑造了我
Nothing made me.

901
00:46:44,970 --> 00:46:46,560
我塑造了自己
I made me.

902
00:46:48,330 --> 00:46:49,510
红胡子
Redbeard?

903
00:46:49,690 --> 00:46:51,470
我的天啊
Good God!

904
00:46:58,020 --> 00:46:59,390
我们该怎么办
What are we to do?

905
00:47:03,970 --> 00:47:05,400
我们去跟她聊聊吧
Why don't we have a chat?

906
00:47:12,600 --> 00:47:14,560
是瑞克莱蒂太太吧
Mrs Ricoletti, I believe!

907
00:47:15,580 --> 00:47:17,710
就这个时节来说  今晚真是宜人
A pleasant night for the time of year, is it not?

908
00:47:17,750 --> 00:47:19,900
这不可能  福尔摩斯  不可能
It cannot be true, Holmes, it cannot!

909
00:47:19,900 --> 00:47:20,980
是不可能
No, it can't.

910
00:47:31,340 --> 00:47:33,150
- 锁上了  - 按照要求锁着
- Is it locked? - As per instruction.

911
00:47:33,180 --> 00:47:34,510
那是打破窗户的声音  是吗
That was a window breaking, wasn't it?

912
00:47:34,510 --> 00:47:36,820
我们只需要担心一扇打破的窗户
There's only one broken window we need concern ourselves with.

913
00:47:48,650 --> 00:47:50,240
- 待在这儿  华生  - 什么  不
- Stay here, Watson. - What? No.

914
00:47:50,240 --> 00:47:52,200
所有进出房子的门窗都锁着
All the doors and windows to the house are locked.

915
00:47:52,250 --> 00:47:54,170
这是他们唯一的出口  我需要你在这儿守着
This is their only way out, I need you here!

916
00:47:54,170 --> 00:47:55,200
但那声音很接近
But the sound was so close.

917
00:47:55,200 --> 00:47:57,490
- 肯定是从房子这一侧传来的  - 守在这儿
- It had to be from this side of the house. - Stay here!

918
00:48:12,560 --> 00:48:13,980
不
No!

919
00:48:21,810 --> 00:48:25,070
你答应过保护他安全的  你答应过的
You promised to keep him safe. You promised!

920
00:48:25,920 --> 00:48:27,260
你...
You...

921
00:48:51,820 --> 00:48:53,680
你是人  这我知道
You're human, I know that.

922
00:48:56,980 --> 00:48:58,230
你肯定是
You must be.

923
00:49:02,590 --> 00:49:06,660
我们这样站在黑暗中也没什么用
Little use us standing here in the dark.

924
00:49:08,070 --> 00:49:11,710
毕竟  这是十九世纪
After all, this is the 19th century.

925
00:49:53,910 --> 00:49:58,300
别忘了我
Do not forget me!

926
00:49:58,970 --> 00:50:03,880
别忘了我
Do not forget me!

927
00:50:10,820 --> 00:50:13,090
- 华生  - 她在那儿  她就在那边
- Watson! - She's there! She's down there!

928
00:50:13,090 --> 00:50:14,540
别告诉我你擅离职守了
Don't tell me you abandoned your post!

929
00:50:14,540 --> 00:50:16,470
什么  福尔摩斯  她在那儿  我看见她了
What? Holmes, she's there, I saw her!

930
00:50:20,930 --> 00:50:22,350
没人了  都怪你
Empty, thanks to you!

931
00:50:23,330 --> 00:50:24,560
煮熟的鸭子飞了
Our bird is flown!

932
00:50:24,570 --> 00:50:27,230
不  福尔摩斯  不是你想的那样
No! No, Holmes, it wasn't what you think.

933
00:50:27,230 --> 00:50:28,640
我看见她了  那鬼魂
I saw her! The ghost!

934
00:50:28,640 --> 00:50:31,180
根本没有鬼魂
There are no ghosts!

935
00:50:34,790 --> 00:50:37,890
发生什么了  尤斯塔斯爵士在哪
What happened? Where is Sir Eustace?

936
00:50:40,050 --> 00:50:41,270
死了
Dead.

937
00:50:44,940 --> 00:50:47,010
你不能怪自己
You really mustn't blame yourself, you know.

938
00:50:48,460 --> 00:50:49,600
是  你说得对
No, you're quite right.

939
00:50:50,290 --> 00:50:51,590
很高兴你明白过来了
I'm glad you're seeing sense.

940
00:50:51,590 --> 00:50:52,900
华生也应该受谴责
Watson is equally culpable.

941
00:50:53,170 --> 00:50:55,370
我们搞砸了整个案子
Between us, we've managed to botch this whole case.

942
00:50:55,390 --> 00:50:57,200
我做出承诺  要保护那个人
I gave an undertaking to protect that man,

943
00:50:57,210 --> 00:50:59,040
结果他现在胸口插着匕首  倒在那里
now he's lying there with a dagger in his breast.

944
00:50:59,040 --> 00:51:01,650
其实  你承诺的是调查他的谋杀案
In fact, you gave an undertaking to investigate his murder.

945
00:51:01,650 --> 00:51:03,980
满怀没这个必要的自信
In the confident expectation I would not have to!

946
00:51:06,770 --> 00:51:08,310
你能告诉我们什么吗  医生
Anything you can tell us, Doctor?

947
00:51:09,100 --> 00:51:12,730
凶手刺杀他的力度可不小
Well, he's been stabbed with considerable force.

948
00:51:12,820 --> 00:51:14,050
这么说  是男性
It's a man, then?

949
00:51:14,850 --> 00:51:16,050
可能是
Possibly.

950
00:51:16,050 --> 00:51:19,020
刀刃非常锋利  所以也可能是女性
A very keen blade, so it could conceivably have been a woman?

951
00:51:19,020 --> 00:51:20,130
从理论上说  是的
In theory, yes,

952
00:51:20,130 --> 00:51:21,840
但我们知道是谁  我看见她了
but we know who it was, I saw her.

953
00:51:21,840 --> 00:51:23,910
- 华生  - 我看见鬼魂了  亲眼所见
- Watson! - I saw the ghost, with my own eyes!

954
00:51:23,910 --> 00:51:26,040
你什么也没看见  你看到了别人做的戏
You saw nothing! You saw what you were supposed to see!

955
00:51:26,040 --> 00:51:27,960
你自己说过的  我没有想象力
You said yourself, I have no imagination.

956
00:51:27,960 --> 00:51:30,120
那就动动脑  去掉不可能的解释
Then use your brain, such as it is, to eliminate the impossible,

957
00:51:30,120 --> 00:51:31,530
在这桩案子中就是鬼魂
which in this case is the ghost,

958
00:51:31,540 --> 00:51:33,870
并观察余下的  那就是答案
and observe what remains, which in this case is a solution

959
00:51:33,870 --> 00:51:36,510
如此明显  连雷斯垂德也能想明白
so blindingly obvious even Lestrade could work it out!

960
00:51:36,600 --> 00:51:37,430
谢谢
Thank you!

961
00:51:37,430 --> 00:51:39,520
别去想什么来自冥界的幽灵了
Forget spectres from the other world!

962
00:51:39,820 --> 00:51:42,670
只有一个嫌疑人有作案动机和机会
There is only one suspect with motive and opportunity.

963
00:51:42,760 --> 00:51:43,990
简直无异于留了字条
They might as well have left a note.

964
00:51:43,990 --> 00:51:45,240
凶手确实留了字条
They did leave a note.

965
00:51:45,300 --> 00:51:47,390
然后还有另一扇破窗的问题
And then there's the matter of the other broken window.

966
00:51:47,390 --> 00:51:50,310
- 什么另一扇破窗  - 就是啊  根本没有
- What other broken window? - Precisely! There isn't one.

967
00:51:50,310 --> 00:51:51,450
整栋房子唯一一扇破窗
The only broken window in this establishment

968
00:51:51,450 --> 00:51:52,950
就是我和华生进来的那扇
is the one that Watson and I entered through,

969
00:51:52,960 --> 00:51:55,090
但在那之前  我们清楚地听见了声音...
yet, prior to that, we distinctly heard the sound of...

970
00:51:55,090 --> 00:51:56,790
- 你刚才说什么  - 你说什么
- What did you just say? - Sorry?

971
00:51:57,260 --> 00:51:59,000
关于字条  你刚才说什么
About a note, what did you just say?

972
00:51:59,150 --> 00:52:01,770
- 我说凶手确实留下了字条  - 不  没有
- I said the murderer DID leave a note. - No, they didn't.

973
00:52:01,870 --> 00:52:04,730
匕首上系了张字条  你肯定看见了
There's a message tied to the dagger. You must have seen it!

974
00:52:04,730 --> 00:52:05,880
- 没有什么字条  - 有的
- There's no message. - Yes!

975
00:52:05,880 --> 00:52:07,730
我发现尸体的时候上面没有字条
There was no message when I found the body.

976
00:52:25,880 --> 00:52:26,790
福尔摩斯
Holmes?

977
00:52:31,010 --> 00:52:31,990
上面写了什么
What is it?

978
00:52:39,180 --> 00:52:43,060
想我了吗

979
00:52:51,370 --> 00:52:52,630
你想吗
Do you?

980
00:52:53,410 --> 00:52:54,620
我想什么
Do I what?

981
00:52:55,720 --> 00:52:57,970
想我了吗

982
00:52:57,800 --> 00:52:59,800
你怎么拿到这个的
H-how did you get that?

983
00:52:59,800 --> 00:53:02,070
我把它留在犯罪现场了
I left it at the crime scene.

984
00:53:02,540 --> 00:53:03,800
犯罪现场
"Crime scene"?

985
00:53:04,050 --> 00:53:06,880
你从哪学来的这些词汇
Where do you pick up these extraordinary expressions?

986
00:53:07,010 --> 00:53:08,280
你想他吗
Do you miss him?

987
00:53:08,690 --> 00:53:10,200
莫里亚蒂已经死了
Moriarty is dead.

988
00:53:10,230 --> 00:53:11,650
但是
And yet...?

989
00:53:13,400 --> 00:53:15,380
我们没找到他的尸体
His body was never recovered.

990
00:53:15,810 --> 00:53:19,920
一个被推下瀑布的数学教授是该找不到
To be expected when one pushes a maths professor over a waterfall.

991
00:53:20,320 --> 00:53:23,270
纯粹理性被惊险的情节推翻
Pure reason toppled by sheer melodrama.

992
00:53:23,270 --> 00:53:24,910
一句话概括了你的生活
Your life in a nutshell.

993
00:53:26,190 --> 00:53:29,080
你从哪学来的这些词汇
Where do you pick up these extraordinary expressions?

994
00:53:43,560 --> 00:53:45,050
你又胖了吗
Have you put on weight?

995
00:53:45,740 --> 00:53:48,570
你昨天才见过我  你觉得可能吗
You saw me only yesterday. Does that seem possible?

996
00:53:48,700 --> 00:53:49,670
不可能
No.

997
00:53:49,680 --> 00:53:51,710
但我的确又胖了
Yet here I am, increased.

998
00:53:51,890 --> 00:53:52,890
全英格兰
What does that tell

999
00:53:52,970 --> 00:53:55,670
最好的犯罪调查专家能从中悟到什么
the foremost criminal investigator in England?

1000
00:53:55,670 --> 00:53:56,650
全英格兰
In England?

1001
00:53:56,650 --> 00:53:57,840
你陷得很深  夏洛克
You're in deep, Sherlock,

1002
00:53:57,840 --> 00:53:59,870
比你预想的要深得多
deeper than you ever intended to be.

1003
00:54:00,000 --> 00:54:02,190
- 你列清单了吗  - 列什么
- Have you made a list? - Of what?

1004
00:54:02,330 --> 00:54:05,930
所有的  我们会需要张清单
Everything. We will need a list.

1005
00:54:11,030 --> 00:54:12,310
好样的
Good boy.

1006
00:54:13,290 --> 00:54:16,120
不  我还没完事
No, I haven't finished yet.

1007
00:54:16,120 --> 00:54:18,630
莫里亚蒂可能不敢苟同
Moriarty may beg to differ.

1008
00:54:20,340 --> 00:54:24,560
他想让我分心  转移我的视线
He's trying to distract me. To derail me.

1009
00:54:24,760 --> 00:54:28,130
没错  他是镜片上的裂纹  药膏里的苍蝇
Yes. He's the crack in the lens, the fly in the ointment,

1010
00:54:28,460 --> 00:54:30,340
数据里的病毒
the virus in the data.

1011
00:54:34,200 --> 00:54:36,660
我必须完成
I have to finish this.

1012
00:54:38,140 --> 00:54:41,550
如果莫里亚蒂真从莱辛巴赫的海釜里爬了出来
If Moriarty has risen from the Reichenbach cauldron,

1013
00:54:42,000 --> 00:54:43,690
他会找到你的
he will seek you out.

1014
00:54:44,730 --> 00:54:46,060
那我等着他
I'll be waiting.

1015
00:54:53,250 --> 00:54:54,550
是啊
Yes.

1016
00:54:58,160 --> 00:55:00,290
恐怕你会的
I'm very much afraid you will.

1017
00:55:15,140 --> 00:55:16,720
尤斯塔斯·卡迈克之死

1018
00:55:18,520 --> 00:55:20,220
马车夫说  "是瑞克莱蒂太太"

1019
00:55:24,890 --> 00:55:27,100
又一位愤怒的新娘

1020
00:55:31,100 --> 00:55:32,810
辉煌一生最终惨死

1021
00:55:31,100 --> 00:55:32,810
汉莫斯诺子爵死亡

1022
00:55:31,100 --> 00:55:32,810
显赫贵族惨遭袭击

1023
00:55:31,100 --> 00:55:32,810
苏格兰场一筹莫展

1024
00:55:35,850 --> 00:55:37,390
下一个是谁

1025
00:55:44,290 --> 00:55:46,790
他已经这样两天了
Two days he's been like that.

1026
00:55:47,550 --> 00:55:48,470
他吃东西了吗
Has he eaten?

1027
00:55:48,470 --> 00:55:50,420
没有  一口都没吃
No, not a morsel.

1028
00:55:51,260 --> 00:55:53,670
媒体都乐疯了
Press are having a ruddy field day.

1029
00:55:53,670 --> 00:55:55,150
外面还有记者蹲守
There's still reporters outside.

1030
00:55:55,150 --> 00:55:57,720
他们一直在那里  我赶不走他们
Oh, they've been there all the time, I can't get rid of them.

1031
00:55:58,000 --> 00:56:01,230
我一直忙着给他们泡茶
I've been rushed off my feet making tea.

1032
00:56:01,630 --> 00:56:03,050
你为什么要给他们泡茶
Why do you make them tea?

1033
00:56:04,130 --> 00:56:06,900
我不知道  我就那么做了
I dunno, I just sort of do.

1034
00:56:08,540 --> 00:56:11,370
他说"只有一个嫌疑人"  然后就走了
He said, "There's only one suspect," and then he just walks away

1035
00:56:11,370 --> 00:56:12,420
现在又不肯解释
and now he won't explain.

1036
00:56:12,420 --> 00:56:15,290
这很奇怪  他最喜欢解释了
Which is strange, because he likes that bit.

1037
00:56:15,290 --> 00:56:17,420
他说这案子很简单  我都能解开
Said it was so simple I could solve it.

1038
00:56:18,570 --> 00:56:20,980
他肯定是在夸大其词
I'm sure he was exaggerating.

1039
00:56:23,340 --> 00:56:24,850
你觉得他在做什么
What's he doing, do you think?

1040
00:56:24,850 --> 00:56:27,240
- 他说他在等待  - 等什么
- He says he's waiting. - For what?

1041
00:56:27,280 --> 00:56:28,640
等魔鬼
The devil.

1042
00:56:30,050 --> 00:56:32,010
这可难说
I wouldn't be surprised.

1043
00:56:32,100 --> 00:56:33,950
来这儿的什么人都有
We get all sorts here.

1044
00:56:35,240 --> 00:56:39,150
- 有变化的话就给我发电报  - 好的
- Well, wire me if there's any change. - Yeah.

1045
00:57:22,170 --> 00:57:25,160
我要说的你都想到了吧
Everything I have to say has already crossed your mind.

1046
00:57:25,160 --> 00:57:28,180
或许我的回答也在你脑中浮现过
Then possibly my answer has crossed yours.

1047
00:57:28,680 --> 00:57:29,940
像颗子弹一样
Like a bullet.

1048
00:57:37,570 --> 00:57:39,030
这个习惯很危险
It's a dangerous habit,

1049
00:57:39,030 --> 00:57:43,150
摸睡衣口袋里上了膛的手枪
to finger loaded firearms in the pocket of one's dressing gown.

1050
00:57:44,000 --> 00:57:46,370
还是你看到我太高兴了
Or are you just pleased to see me?

1051
00:57:51,390 --> 00:57:53,060
请原谅我准备了些预防措施
You'll forgive me for taking precautions.

1052
00:57:53,060 --> 00:57:54,910
你没准备的话我会生气的
I'd be offended if you didn't.

1053
00:57:54,910 --> 00:57:58,480
当然  我也礼尚往来了
Obviously, I've returned the courtesy.

1054
00:58:07,130 --> 00:58:09,080
我喜欢你的房间
I like your rooms.

1055
00:58:09,650 --> 00:58:11,780
散发着如此
They smell so...

1056
00:58:14,190 --> 00:58:15,250
阳刚的气息
manly.

1057
00:58:16,210 --> 00:58:19,170
想必你在此之前就来过了
I'm sure you acquainted yourself with them before now.

1058
00:58:19,180 --> 00:58:20,900
毕竟你总不在这里
Well, you are always away,

1059
00:58:20,930 --> 00:58:23,230
总在为《斯特兰德月刊》探险
on your little adventures for The Strand.

1060
00:58:23,460 --> 00:58:26,150
跟我说说  插画师和你一起出行吗
Tell me, does the illustrator travel with you?

1061
00:58:26,220 --> 00:58:29,800
你推理的时候  还要摆造型吗
Do you have to pose... during your deductions?

1062
